<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF6E6AD1FA469ACA19ACB67F" pageId="149" pageNumber="910" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF6E6AD1FA469ACA19ACB67F" blockId="149.[1464,2670,3180,3486]" pageId="149" pageNumber="910">
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF6E6AD1FA469ACA1BE8B782" box="[1466,1512,3219,3248]" country="South Sudan" name="Lakes" pageId="149" pageNumber="910">See</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF6E6AD1FA089ACA1892B782" baseAuthorityName="Scully" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1524,1682,3219,3248]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="910" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tubinaris">M. tubinaris</taxonomicName>
. Limited genetic data suggest 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF6E6AD1F7CB9ACA1694B782" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1891" box="[2103,2196,3219,3248]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Harpiocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="916" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="feae">M. feae</taxonomicName>
may be closelyrelated to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF6E6AD1F6059ACA1BE7B7E5" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="915" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beelzebub">M. beelzebub</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF6E6AD1F9D09AEF18E9B7E5" box="[1580,1769,3254,3287]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="910" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annamitica">M. annamitica</taxonomicName>
; see also M. jaintiana. Typically treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF6E6AD1F6189AEF1465B7E5" authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1872" box="[2532,2661,3254,3287]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="919" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurata">M. aurata</taxonomicName>
, but is now considered a distinct species. Includes populations of 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF6E6AD1F6BB9A8717D4B7CD" box="[2375,2516,3294,3327]" country="Botswana" name="South East" pageId="149" pageNumber="910">South-east</collectingRegion>
Asia previously placed in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF6E6AD1F9739B5C192CB614" baseAuthorityName="Scully" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1679,1836,3333,3366]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="910" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tubinaris">M. tubinaris</taxonomicName>
that were separated in 2011 as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF6E6AD1F7259B5C1776B614" authorityName="Csorba &amp; Furey" authorityYear="2011" box="[2265,2422,3333,3366]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="916" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cineracea">M. cineracea</taxonomicName>
, but subsequently found to refer to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF6E6AD1F9559B751905B67F" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1891" box="[1705,1797,3372,3405]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Harpiocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="916" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="feae">M. feae</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
